Experiment No: 02
Name of Experiment: Basic Linux Command.
Object: Our aim is to learn basic Linux command with Linux mint operating system.
Command:
1) whoami: It shows who logged on this system.
Basic syntax: whoami
Output:
2) hostname: It tells on which machine you are.
Basic syntax: hostname
Output:
3) pwd: It shows the path of current working director.
Basic syntax: pwd
Output:
4) cd : It brings us to the highest level of your home directory of computer
Basic syntax: cd
Output:
5) cd .. : It moves one directory up.
Basic syntax: cd ..
Output:
6) cd ../ ../ : It moves two directories up (and so on)
Basic syntax: cd ../ ../
Output:
7) cd <dir_name> : It switches to 'dir_name' directory
Basic syntax: cd Desktop
Output:
8) ls : It displays the list of files in the current working directory
Basic syntax: ls
Output:
9) mkdir <dir_name>:It creates a directory with specified 'dir_name'.
Basic syntax: mkdir labreport
Output:
10) touch: It creates files.
Basic syntax: touch myfile.txt
Output:
11) find: It finds out file from a specific directory.
Basic syntax: find Desktop/labreport/profile.txt
Output:
12) vi: It views a file contents.
Basic syntax: vi profile.txt
Output:
13) mv <name1> <name2>: It renames the directories or files.
Basic syntax: mv myfile.txt profile
Output:
14) cp <name> <path> : It copies file/directory as specified in path
Basic syntax: mv myfile.txt profile
Output:
15) rmdir <dir_name> : It removes entire directory.
Basic syntax: rmdir Dept
Output:
16) rm <file_name> : It removes file name.
Basic syntax: rm pi.txt
Output:
Conclusion: In this lab experiment, we learn about linux basic command. It helps us to develop
future project in Linux operating system.
